Reasoning: The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of stochastic geometry to model the locations of spatially NOMA users suggests a focus on system-level analysis and optimization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the consideration of diversity analysis and the comparison of different NOMA schemes suggests a focus on multimedia systems and applications (cs.MM).
